    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="799"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./10–1044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Representative on the Advisory Council for
                        Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-10T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 10, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 10—7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>700. Italian Foreign Office, having received information of increasing German
                    persecutions in northern Italy involving barbarous tortures and massacre of
                    hostages, has asked ACC<note n="41" xml:id="d799fn41">Allied Control Commission
                        for Italy.</note> whether fresh warning could not be given Germany that such
                    conduct will not pass unnoticed. It proposes that such a warning be given by
                    Allies and Italian Government simultaneously and publicized through radio and
                    press. ACC will be instructed to inform Foreign Office that question has been
                    referred to the two Governments.</p>
                <p>Text of Italian memo of particulars sent by pouch.<note n="42" xml:id="d799fn42"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
